	   <tr><td colspan=2>Listen to this guy.&nbsp;&nbsp;I just fought Miragul with a bunch of friends.  We had 3 full groups and an incomplete fourth.  Our only death was a 52 druid who aggroed with starfire too early.  Miragul dropped him in one nuke.  Buff up as much as you can.  His DoTs are NASTY.  You need hp for your tanks more than anything else.  Once his nasty DoT mana runs out his melee is no slouch.  Hitting in the high 100's all the time.  He has TONS of hp so even if you survive the DoTs you need the extra hp to wear him all the way down.  Make sure he's charmed or mezzed when you hand in the phylactery.  Con him and make sure you're indifferent before you click the trade button or he will eat it.  That is all. Good luck.  I looted a nice head and robe from him.<br><br>Funny, I'm a 54th Dwarven Paladin myself.  We rule! Go Tramddark!<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
