	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'm going to have to disagree. Don't know if you're being sarcastic, but this robe is definately NOT worth it for any caster. Just to get in on a dragon raid, you usually must be level 46 to 52. Most casters have better equipment by then. Supposing you don't, the books are almost always allowed to be rolled on only by paladins. So, you must be in a situation where:<br><br>a) You are of right level to attend dragon raids.<br>b) The book drops off Vox / Nagafen.<br>c) No paladins are there to loot, or caster-rolling is allowed.<br>d) You must win both rolls.<br>e) You must gather 3 or more groups of 46 or higher characters to kill Miragul.<br><br>Easily the bottleneck of the paladin epic, this robe stats don't suck, but aren't too great either, and getting some of the best caster robes in the game are arguably easier. This robe admittadly does look neat, but this fashion is probably one of the most rare in the entire game.<br><br>What I wonder is, if this guy is such an incredible necromancer, how come he is wearing this mediocre cloak? =)<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
